-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                             ==== INSTALL ====

                               -- wxCron --
                              Version 0.2.0
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

There is no need for a install routine. Just unpack all files to a directory
and start the binary (wxCron.exe on windows).
On first start wxCron will create a configuration file ("wxCron.conf"),
a log file ("wxCron.log") and a timestamp file ("wxCron.tsmp"). That's all!

Please feel free to contact me if you need more informations!

FILE & DIRECTORY LISTING
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 README         - general instructions
 INSTALL        - installation instructions (this file)
 LICENSE        - license information
 HISTORY        - history of wxCron development
 CREDITS        - all persons, projects and institutions
                  related to this project
 CHANGELOG      - differences between the blackfisk versions
 HELP			- help file for wxCron
 wxCron.exe  	- the windows (32bit) binary
 crontab        - the crontab file where you can define the jobs
 wxCron.conf	- configuration file for wxCron
 wxCron.tsmp	- timestamp file to remember the last job execution
 graphic/       - icons and other graphic stuff for wxCron

 -- (extra files and directories in the source package) --
 include/				- wxCron header files
 src/					- wxCron source files
 graphic/src			- SVG source files for graphic stuff
 build/					- project-files for different build-environments
 build/README			- informations how to build wxCron
 build/wxCron.workspace - workspace file for the IDE Code::Blocks
 build/wxCron.cbp  		- project file for the IDE Code::Blocks
 build/wxCron.sln		- workspace (solution) file for IDE MSVC++ 2008 Express Edition
 build/wxCron.vcproj	- project file for IDE MSVC++ 2008 Express Edition
 TODO					- This is just a little TODO list for wxCron.
						  Please use the bugtracking-system on BerliOS instead
						  of this file.
